## IMPLEMENTATION ORDER

Build in this exact sequence:

1. `.env` + `agent/config.py` + `docker-compose.yml` → environment working
2. `agent/obsidian/folder_policy.py` → access rules defined before anything else
3. `agent/privacy/` (scrubber + classifier + metadata_strip) → privacy layer
4. `agent/rag/embedder.py` + `agent/rag/store.py` → vector DB working
5. `agent/obsidian/ingester.py` → ingest your vault, verify in Qdrant UI
6. `agent/obsidian/vault.py` → read/write notes
7. `agent/llm/openrouter.py` → test a simple LLM call
8. `agent/graph/state.py` + `agent/graph/edges.py` → graph skeleton
9. **Graph nodes one at a time** (intake → classifier → retriever → reranker → confidence_check → tool_router → llm_answer → store_response → learner)
10. `agent/graph/graph.py` → wire nodes into graph, compile
11. `agent/mcp/filesystem_tools.py` → test filesystem tool
12. `agent/mcp/apify_tools.py` → test Apify tool
13. `agent/memory/long_term.py` → SQLite memory
14. `agent/cli.py` → full CLI loop
15. `agent/scheduler/digest.py` → nightly digest
16. `tests/` → run privacy + graph tests

